Bring a large pot of water to a boil. In a large skillet saute garlic in olive oil, until slightly yellow in color. Add kale and saute for 3-4 minutes; season with salt and pepper. Add chicken broth and reduce by half. Add heavy cream and bring to a simmer; reduce until thickened. Cook pasta according to package directions; drain and toss with sauce. Remove from the heat and stir in cheese and pine nuts.